Description: This is a single owner Jackson USA Custom Shop RR24 guitar and has been stored in a smoke-free home. The guitar pictured for sale in this auction is a case queen and has not been been played very much. It has an Alder body guitar and features a single Seymour Duncan TB-5 (Custom 5), ebony fret board with 24 stain less steel frets.The overall condition is excellent - No nicks, scratches, buckle rash or wing dings. I used this guitar to play heavy music and it has been setup using 11-51 DAddario strings, currently tuned to D standard. It will come with the Jackson case it came with and it is also in excellent condition. Additional items included are: the original back tremplate, tremarm and original hang tag. Please see pics and feel free to ask any questions! The packaging for this guitar is a large (big box) so shipping will be $50 insured. Sorry no international shipping, USA - lower 48 ONLY.
